{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"949d","heading":"Sessions","label":"949d Sessions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptII/ch47A/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsA prior section 949d, added , , , related to sessions of military commissions, prior to the general amendment of this chapter by .Pub. L. 109–366, § 3(a)(1)120 Stat. 2611Pub. L. 111–84Oct. 17, 2006"],"amendments":["Prior ProvisionsA prior section 949d, added , , , related to sessions of military commissions, prior to the general amendment of this chapter by .Pub. L. 109–366, § 3(a)(1)120 Stat. 2611Pub. L. 111–84Oct. 17, 2006"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Sessions Without Presence of Members","label":"a .—Sessions Without Presence of Members","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"hearing and determining motions raising defenses or objections which are capable of determination without trial of the issues raised by a plea of not guilty;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"hearing and ruling upon any matter which may be ruled upon by the military judge under this chapter, whether or not the matter is appropriate for later consideration or decision by the members;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if permitted by regulations prescribed by the Secretary of Defense, receiving the pleas of the accused; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"performing any other procedural function which may be performed by the military judge under this chapter or under rules prescribed pursuant to and which does not require the presence of the members.section 949a of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in subsections (b), (c), and (d), any proceedings under paragraph (1) shall be conducted in the presence of the accused, defense counsel, and trial counsel, and shall be made part of the record.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Deliberation or Vote of Members","label":"b .—Deliberation or Vote of Members","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"When the members of a military commission under this chapter deliberate or vote, only the members may be present.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Closure of Proceedings","label":"c .—Closure of Proceedings","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The military judge may close to the public all or part of the proceedings of a military commission under this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"protect information the disclosure of which could reasonably be expected to cause damage to the national security, including intelligence or law enforcement sources, methods, or activities; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensure the physical safety of individuals.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A finding under paragraph (2) may be based upon a presentation, including a presentation ex parte or in camera, by either trial counsel or defense counsel.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Exclusion of Accused From Certain Proceedings","label":"d .—Exclusion of Accused From Certain Proceedings","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to ensure the physical safety of individuals; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s949d/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs949d%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to prevent disruption of the proceedings by the accused.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
